<title>GERMANY: Mercedes signs deal with workforce.</title>
<headline>Mercedes signs deal with workforce.</headline>
<dateline>STUTTGART, Germany 1997-02-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mercedes-Benz has agreed a contract with its labour force that will protect employees from layoffs through the year 2000, management board member Heiner Tropitzsch said on Friday.</p>
<p>The deal, agreed with Mercedes-Benz's works council, effects 134,000 employees. The package included a provision that future wage increases would be formulated on a more restricted basis than they have in the past.</p>
<p>Mercedes also said it would not increase its workforce by the year 2000, he said.</p>
